                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.002/29.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-08T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1913—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>315. De la Barra resigned the position of Minister of Foreign Affairs today. The
                    Department should advise me as to my attitude toward the new Minister. I have
                    not yet ascertained the cause of De la Barra’s resignation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
